SETUP

WebXR is not a game engine. Use WebGL under the hood. Use another interface (three.js?) to interface with WebGL and provide camera view

WebXR API emulator
https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/webxr-api-emulator/mjddjgeghkdijejnciaefnkjmkafnnje/

Types of WebXR interfaces
- immersive-vr: put it onto headset
- immersive-ar: not widely supported
- inline: in the browser

Everything in a 2x2 cube
No concept of camera, modify the viewMatrix in the opposite direction


Run a web server from Chrome
https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/web-server-for-chrome/ofhbbkphhbklhfoeikjpcbhemlocgigb/

Logging
console.log("selectstart " + currently_selected_boxes);
Look at stuff in the console

Documentation
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebXR_Device_API

WHAT TO DO


1. Make the boxes stay after you release them

2. If the two boxes are within 0.25 m of each other, change their colors to white

Hints:
box.node is an ID number